<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870421-0058 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:McDonnell Douglas Corp.</HL><DD> 04/21/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MD </IN><TEXT>   MCDONNELL DOUGLAS CORP. Chairman Sanford N. McDonnell told the annual meeting the company expects to report first-quarter earnings fell 30% to about $43 million, or 1.06 a share. Sales totaled $3 billion, he said, about equal with a year earlier. He cited a nonrecurring charge of $37.6 million to cover early retirement programs at four units of the St. Louis-based maker of defense, aerospace and computer products. </TEXT></DOC>